        "summary": "## Goal\n1. **Retry failed Morning Brief cron job** — Done, ran successfully\n2. **Finish The OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.** — $9 PDF, write/complete Sections 7-10, compile final PDF\n3. **Build \"Telephone\"** — Voice-first communication tool with fairy lights, system voice responses, local-only\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Guide: $9, PDF only, no audio, no sales page yet — priority is finishing the PDF content\n- All Telegram links must use `[text](url)` format with LAN IP (192.168.1.162) to be clickable on phone\n- Voice memos: system default voice (no `-v` flag), MP3 format via `say` + ffmpeg, sent via `message action=send asVoice=true`\n- When Bobby reports a problem, fix immediately and note it\n- Keep replies short, conversational, easy to answer back\n- Telephone must use: Safari, toggle mic, audio only, tap to replay, dark theme, fairy lights with 3 different formations for (speaking / thinking / replying)\n- Telephone: completely local, separate from the guide/questionnaire project\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Morning Brief retried and ran successfully (gave full weather/bible/calendar/reminders briefing)\n- [x] Created `~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/questionnaire.html` for author questions\n- [x] Added clickable-link rule and voice memo format rules to `TOOLS.md`\n- [x] Consulted Rex for guide title — Rex's top pick: \"The OpenClaw Playbook: Build Your First AI Automation in 30 Minutes (No Coding Required)\"\n- [x] Built Telephone: `telephone.html`, `server.js` (port 8791), `dean.js` background processor\n- [x] HTTP server on port 8790, Node server on port 8791, dean.js background process — all running\n- [x] Opened `telephone.html` in browser for Bobby\n- [x] Question about why I sent a voice memo — apologized and sent clickable link instead\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Telephone: \"Speech not supported\"** — Web Speech API (SpeechRecognition) not working in Safari. Needs fix.\n\n### Blocked\n- [ ] Guide: Sections 7-10 are stubs/incomplete — need Bobby to fill out questionnaire first, then write content\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **LAN IP format for Telegram links**: `http://192.168.1.162:PORT` — Bobby can't click localhost URLs from his phone, so all links use LAN IP\n- **Voice memo pipeline**: `say \"text\" -o /tmp/voice.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/voice.aiff /tmp/voice.mp3 -y` → send with `message action=send asVoice=true`\n- **Telephone architecture**: \n  - `telephone.html` (port 8790) — frontend with mic toggle, fairy lights canvas, SpeechRecognition\n  - `server.js` (port 8791) — receives transcribed text, stores in `messages.json`, serves audio files, has `/talk`, `/messages`, `/reply`, `/audio/` endpoints\n  - `dean.js` — background process polling `/messages`, calling OpenClaw Gateway at port 8787 for responses, generating TTS audio via `say`, posting to `/reply`\n- **OpenClaw Gateway**: Running on port 8787, accepts chat completions at `/v1/chat/completions` with model `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`\n- **Telephone messages**: Stored at `~/Desktop/Telephone/messages.json`\n- **Guide folder**: `~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/` — Sections 1-6 complete, Section 7 complete (Morning Brief content) but file ends with 3 placeholder stubs for Sections 8-9-10, Sections 8/9/10 exist as separate complete files but structure is confusing\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Fix \"Speech not supported\" in Safari for Telephone** — SpeechRecognition API may not be available or needs different approach (possibly use `annyang` library or fallback to press-to-transcribe)\n2. **Get Bobby to fill out questionnaire** — [http://192.168.1.162:8790/questionnaire.html](http://192.168.1.162:8790/questionnaire.html)\n3. **Write Sections 7-10** — Fill in placeholder stubs in Section 7, verify Sections 8-10 content, assemble final guide\n4. **Compile PDF** — Use existing compiled HTML/WeasyPrint workflow or similar\n5. **Test Telephone** — Once speech recognition works, test full voice loop: mic on → speak → Dean responds via TTS → fairy lights react\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Questionnaire**: `http://192.168.1.162:8790/questionnaire.html` (port 8790 HTTP server)\n- **Telephone**: `http://192.168.1.162:8790/telephone.html` (same HTTP server, API on 8791)\n- **Telephone server**: Node.js on port 8791; dean.js polling on port 8787\n- **Guide folder**: `~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/`\n- **TOOLS.md**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md`\n- **Message tool for Telegram**: `target=8212808444`, `channel=telegram`\n- **Current Telephone status**: Page loads in Safari but shows \"Speech not supported\" — the Web Speech API (`window.SpeechRecognition || window.webkitSpeechRecognition`) is not available or not permitted in Safari\n- **Bobby's Telegram ID**: 8212808444\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Progress-Notes.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-1-What-is-OpenClaw.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-10-Money-Making-Use-Cases.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-7-Your-First-Automation.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-8-Real-World-Workflows.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-9-Advanced-Techniques.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/questionnaire.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/poller.sh\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/server.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.sh\n</modified-files>",
